he Sender thread's sendProducerData() method (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:357) retrieves ready batches from the accumulator and calls sendProduceRequest() (line 864) to create a ProduceRequest. (4) sendProduceRequest() constructs the ProduceRequest and calls NetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541) to transmit it over the network. (5) On the broker side, ReplicaManager.appendRecords() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala:674) handles the incoming ProduceRequest and delegates to appendRecordsToLeader() (line 627), which in turn calls appendToLocalLog() (line 1370). (6) appendToLocalLog() retrieves the partition and calls partition.appendRecordsToLeader() to write the records to the broker's log. This completes the end-to-end flow from producer to broker's persistent log.\"\n}\n",
